üîß Engineering & Technology

Engineering and Technology is a field focused on applying scientific principles, mathematics, and technology to design, build, and improve machines, systems, software, and infrastructure. It involves problem-solving, innovation, and practical application of knowledge to create solutions for real-world challenges. Students study technical concepts through hands-on projects and experiments to understand how things work and how to make them better.

ü©∫ Medical & Healthcare

Medical and Healthcare is a field dedicated to understanding the human body, diagnosing diseases, and improving health. It involves the study of biology, anatomy, physiology, and medical sciences, combined with practical skills for patient care and treatment. Students learn how medical knowledge can be applied to prevent, treat, and manage illnesses, and how healthcare systems function to maintain the well-being of communities.

üî¨ Science

Science is a field focused on exploring and understanding the natural world through observation, experimentation, and analysis. It involves studying subjects such as physics, chemistry, mathematics, and biology to discover patterns, principles, and laws that govern the universe. Students develop analytical thinking, research skills, and the ability to solve complex problems by applying scientific methods.

üíº Commerce & Business

Commerce and Business is a field that deals with trade, finance, accounting, and the management of economic activities. Students learn how businesses operate, how financial decisions are made, and how resources are managed efficiently. It involves studying subjects such as economics, accounting, taxation, and management principles to understand how organizations function and make profit.

üé® Arts & Humanities

Arts and Humanities is a field that studies human society, culture, communication, and behavior. It involves exploring subjects like literature, history, sociology, political science, and philosophy to understand human experiences and social systems. Students develop critical thinking, communication, and analytical skills to interpret the world and society around them.

‚öñÔ∏è Law

Law is a field focused on understanding legal systems, rights, justice, and governance. It involves studying constitutions, statutes, legal procedures, and ethical considerations to ensure fairness and order in society. Students learn how laws are made, interpreted, and applied, and how legal knowledge can be used to resolve disputes and protect rights.

üé≠ Creative, Design & Media

Creative, Design, and Media is a field centered on visual communication, creativity, and storytelling. It involves developing skills in design, digital media, animation, content creation, and other artistic forms to communicate ideas and experiences. Students learn how creativity can be applied to produce engaging, functional, and aesthetic solutions in media and design industries.

üè® Hospitality, Travel & Services

Hospitality, Travel, and Services is a field that focuses on managing customer experiences, tourism, and service-oriented businesses. Students learn about hotel operations, tourism management, event planning, and client service, gaining practical skills to organize and manage experiences for individuals and organizations in various service industries.

üå± Agriculture & Environmental Studies

Agriculture and Environmental Studies is a field that emphasizes sustainable farming, food production, environmental protection, and natural resource management. Students study the science behind crop production, soil and water management, environmental conservation, and innovative agricultural technologies to support sustainable development and ecological balance.

üéñÔ∏è Defence & Public Services

Defence and Public Services is a field dedicated to national security, public administration, and governance. Students learn leadership, discipline, organizational management, and strategic thinking required for serving the nation, managing public resources, and ensuring the safety and well-being of communities through structured and systematic service roles.